        "text": "The document page is from the New York ISO Ancillary Services Manual and outlines the pricing structure for 30-Minute Reserves in different regions: Eastern, Southeastern, New York City, and Long Island. \n\n1. **Eastern, Southeastern, New York City, or Long Island 30-Minute Reserves**: \n   - If the reserve requirement is less than or equal to the target level, the price is $40/MW.\n   - For other quantities, the price is $0/MW.\n\n2. **Southeastern, New York City, or Long Island 30-Minute Reserves**:\n   - If the requirement is less than or equal to the target level minus any incremental reserve target, the price is $500/MW.\n   - For other quantities, the price is $0/MW.\n\n3. **New York City 30-Minute Reserves**:\n   - If the requirement is less than or equal to the target level for that location, the price is $25/MW.\n   - For other quantities, the price is $0/MW.\n\n4. **Long Island 30-Minute Reserves**:\n   - If the requirement is less than or equal to the target level, the price is $25/MW.\n   - For other quantities, the price is $0/MW.\n\nThe NYISO may adjust the quantity and price of reserves to address operational or reliability issues, with potential temporary modifications lasting up to ninety days. Any changes will involve consultation with relevant committees and regulatory bodies.",
