        "text": "The document page presents data on uplift costs from guarantee payments in New York, categorized by region and year (2018-2019). The chart shows costs in millions of dollars for New York City, Long Island, East Upstate, West Upstate, and Imports, with a total for each year. In 2019, the total was $52 million, down from $77 million in 2018. Long Island's costs remained stable at $15 million each year, with a significant portion (67%) attributed to high-cost peaking resources managing congestion and voltage needs. Recommendations include modeling specific constraints to improve market efficiency and reliability.",
