        "text": "The document is a form related to the New York ISO (NYISO) Capacity Market Products. It requires the following information:\n\n1. **New Resource Load Zone**: Identification of the NYCA Load Zone for a resource located within or outside the NYCA.\n2. **New Resource Transmission Node PTID**: The PTID to which the aggregation electrically maps.\n3. **Facility ID(s)**: NYISO-issued Facility ID numbers for all individual DERs in the aggregation that is the prospective ICAP Supplier.\n\nThe form includes spaces for a signature, customer employee name, title, and phone number.\n\nA footnote (FN 1) explains the notification requirements. It states that the notification must be received by NYISO no later than 5:00 P.M. on the first business day of the month that is two months prior to the month indicated in the notice. For example, to qualify for participation in May, the notification must be received by 5:00 P.M. on the first business day of March.",
